About

Hello,

I'm Sonja!

I am an undergraduate Computer Science and Piano student at the University of British Columbia. I have a passion for UX/UI design, software development, and music. I enjoy working on projects that could have a positive social impact on the world.

I am an undergraduate Computer Science and Piano student at the University of British Columbia. I have a passion for UX/UI design, software development, and music. I enjoy working on projects that could have a positive social impact on the world.

Design and UX/UI

Where Ideas Take Shape

I specialize in designing intuitive, user-centric interfaces. Using tools like Figma, Framer, and Canva, I create experiences that are both visually appealing and highly functional. From wireframes to high-fidelity prototypes, I focus on clarity, accessibility, and seamless interaction.

Software and Data

Building with Purpose
